                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Record of the proceedings of the tribunal of arbitration at
                        the seventeenth conference, held at Geneva, in Switzerland, on the</hi> 5<hi
                        rend="italic">th of August</hi>, 1872.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>Geneva, Switzerland</placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1872-08-05">August 5, 1872</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <seg type="margin">Oral argument of Mr. Evarts.</seg> The conference was held
                    pursuant to adjournment. All the arbitrators and the agents of the two
                    governments were present. The protocol of the last conference was read and
                    approved, and was signed by the president and secretary of the tribunal and the
                    agents of the two governments.</p>
                <p>The tribunal proceeded with the hearing of the oral argument by Mr. Evarts,
                    counsel of the United States, in reply to the argument presented <pb facs="0044"
                        n="32" xml:id="pg_32"/> by Sir Roundell Palmer, counsel of Her Britannic
                    Majesty, at the fifteenth conference.</p>
                <p>The tribunal then adjourned until Tuesday, the 6th instant, at half past 12
                    o’clock.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>FREDERICK SCLOPIS.</item>
                            <item>J. C. BANCROFT DAYIS.</item>
                            <item>TENTERDEN.</item>
                            <item>ALEX. FAVROT, <hi rend="italic">Secretary</hi>.</item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
